Okay so here is the line-by-line explanation:-

The starting part:-
The seashore are calm, safe and quiet. But a human is not made for that. A human has much more potential than that.A true sailor is one who is not afraid to go into the dangerous depths of the ocean.

The Rap explanation:-
The first line and second line conveys that while staying on the shore we can achieve only small things. Our dreams too will be small. If we always stay in our comfort zone, we may be able to survive but we won't be able to be successful 

The next few lines emphasis that a true sailor (khalasi ) will go into the depths of the ocean no matter how dangerous it is. The one who has the courage and guts to take risks are the one who attains success.
